#: ../../source/introduction.rst:4
msgid ""
"The **open H**\\ ome **A**\\ utomation **B**\\ us (openHAB) is an open "
"source, technology agnostic home automation platform which runs as the "
"center of your smart home!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/introduction.rst:9
msgid "Some of openHAB’s strengths are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/introduction.rst:11
msgid ""
"Its ability to integrate a multitude of other devices and systems. "
"openHAB includes other home automation systems, (smart) devices and other"
" technologies into a single solution"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/introduction.rst:14
msgid ""
"To provide a uniform user interface and a common approach to automation "
"rules across the entire system, regardless of the number of manufacturers"
" and sub-systems involved"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/introduction.rst:17
msgid ""
"Giving you the most flexible tool available to make almost any home "
"automation wish come true; if you can think it, odds are that you can "
"implement it with openHAB."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/introduction.rst:22
msgid "What You Need to Know Before You Start"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/introduction.rst:24
msgid ""
"**When home automation just seems to work, it is always the result of "
"hard work.** Home automation is fascinating and requires a considerable "
"investment of your time. Here are some key considerations especially for "
"new users. To be successful, you will need to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/introduction.rst:29
msgid "Start slowly and one step at a time"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/introduction.rst:30
msgid "Be prepared to learn"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/introduction.rst:31
msgid "Remain flexible in how you want to achieve your goal"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/introduction.rst:32
msgid "Celebrate all the small successes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/introduction.rst:34
msgid ""
"Remember, openHAB is just a computer program. The computer will only do "
"what *you* tell it to do. openHAB can provide many default solutions that"
" are easy to setup. On the flip side, the more you insist that everything"
" should look and work exactly the way you want it, the more work you will"
" have to invest. openHAB is fully customizable, but doing so will require"
" substantial effort on your part."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/introduction.rst:41
msgid "After you have read the documentation for openHAB, you will have:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/introduction.rst:43
msgid "Identified a computer on which to run openHAB"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/introduction.rst:44
msgid ""
"Learned how to install openHAB, as well as all other software that is "
"needed to run openHAB (e.g., JAVA)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/introduction.rst:46
msgid ""
"Learned how your smart devices communicate with openHAB; how to make "
"openHAB give commands to your smart devices; and how you can interact "
"with openHAB"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/introduction.rst:50
msgid ""
"Keep your focus. For almost everything, there is more than one way in "
"openHAB to achieve a goal or perform a task. Initially, this can be "
"frustrating and confusing, but it also gives great flexibility and does "
"not mandate the use of certain devices or tools."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/introduction.rst:55
msgid ""
"You may need to learn more about computers than you currently do. But "
"this may not be a problem as you are reading the documentation of "
"software that will enable you to do home automation yourself."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/introduction.rst:59
msgid "Lastly, be prepared to start a new hobby: home automation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/introduction.rst:61
msgid ""
"Basic functions can be achieved in openHAB rather quickly, e.g., switch "
"lights on at a certain time. Others will require much more effort and "
"thought, e.g., how do I determine that someone is home, including guests,"
" but not counting pets? The openHAB forum is a great place to learn and "
"discuss."
msgstr ""

