#: ../../source/introduction.rst:284
msgid ""
"A final word for the DIY enthusiasts. openHAB is very flexible and can "
"support many DIY devices. However, you will quickly realize that DIY "
"often literally means that you *“do it yourself”*. Working with DIY "
"solutions often requires a deeper level of understanding, as well as more"
" patience and perseverance than the integration of ready-to-use devices "
"from commercial providers. The choice is yours of course, but you will "
"need to be prepared to spend either money or time (and sometimes both) to"
" make your home automation goals a reality. And quite often, the "
"investment will be significant."
